title: Fraserburgh United F.C.
text: Fraserburgh United Football Club are a <a href="Scotland">Scottish</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> club from the town of <a href="Fraserburgh">Fraserburgh</a>, <a href="Aberdeenshire">Aberdeenshire</a>. Members of the <a href="Scottish%20Junior%20Football%20Association">Scottish Junior Football Association</a>, they currently play in the <a href="Scottish%20Junior%20Football%20North%20First%20Division">North First Division</a>. Founded in 1976, United are the smaller of the local teams after <a href="Fraserburgh%20F.C.">Fraserburgh F.C.</a> of the <a href="Highland%20Football%20League">Highland League</a>. The club are based at College Park and their colours are tangerine and black.
